name: Clock Toolbar and Header status for User Login
format:
<script id="titleScript" type="text/javascript">
    $(function() {
        // Check if .md-toolbar-tools element exists
        if($('.md-toolbar-tools').length){
            // Initialize the header status element
            initHeader();
            // Load the clock
            loadClock();
        } else {
            // If .md-toolbar-tools element does not exist, try again after 500ms
            setTimeout(function() {
                initHeader();
                loadClock();
            }, 500);
        }
    });

    // Function to initialize the header status element
    function initHeader(){
        if (!$('#headerStatus').length) {
            var toolbar = $('.md-toolbar-tools');
            var div = $('<div/>');
            var k = $('<k id="headerStatus" />');
            // Set the margin to align the element to the left of the header
            // margin align is described as { top, right, bottom, left}
            div[0].style.margin = '5px auto 5px 20px';
            div.append(k);
            toolbar.append(div);
        }
    }

    // Function to load the clock
    function loadClock(){
        $('#clock').remove();
        var toolbar = $('.md-toolbar-tools');
        
        var div = $('<div/>');
        var p = $('<p/ id="clock">');
        
        div.append(p);
        // Set the margin to align the element to the right of the header
        div[0].style.margin = '5px 5px 5px auto';
        toolbar.append(div);

        function upTime() {
            var d = new Date();
            //display the clock as dd/mm/yyyy  + timestamp
            var formattedDate = d.toLocaleDateString("en-GB")+ " " + d.toLocaleTimeString();
            p.text(formattedDate);
        }

        if(document.clockInterval){ 
            clearInterval(document.clockInterval);
            document.clockInterval = null;
        }
            
        document.clockInterval = setInterval(upTime,1000);
    }
</script>

<style>
    #headerStatus {
        font-weight: bold;
        text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    #headerStatus.Logged in as Admin {
        color: lime;
    }

    #headerStatus.No current user {
        color: red;
    }
</style>

<Style id="dashboard-customm-styles">

:root{
    --base-color:#8D8C8C;
    --shadow-dark:0, 0, 0;

    --widgetColor:#cccccc;

    --accentColor:#6a87a3;
   
    
    --h1:10px;

    var(--h2) var(--v2) var(--blur2) 0 rgba(var(--shadow-light), 0.25);

md-slider .md-thumb {

name: Important Programming Notes
info:
Updated on 12/1/2023
To store a memory in NodeRED use global memory to store the value, so that we can call the memory elsewhere within the project.

Function 
to retrieve the memory use: example-
global.get(var1)

to set the global memory use: example-
global.set(var1,msg.payload);
